news.title: PAG raises $4 billion in Asia-focused real estate fund
news.para: The new fund will focus primarily on Japan with a minimum allocation of 60%, said Phi Le, partner and co-head of real assets at PAG.

news.title: Tribeca signs joint development pact for three-acre project in Pune
news.para: The Indian real estate sector is witnessing a rising trend of joint development agreements as developers and landowners seek capital-efficient growth strategies amid evolving market dynamics.

news.title: Housing sales rise by 4% in tier II cities: Report
news.para: The housing sales stood at 1,71,903 units while sales value stood at Rs 1,27,505 crore in 2023.

news.title: Nexus Select Trust completes acquisition of Bengaluru's Vega City Mall for Rs 913 crore
news.para: The acquisition is accretive and is expected to generate retail net operating income of Rs 78 crore. This is Nexus Select Trust's fourth asset in Bengaluru.

news.title: Rudrapur’s new mayor vows smart city transformation
news.para: Regarding his plans to make Rudrapur a smart city, he stated, "A smart city requires modern infrastructure and sustainable energy solutions.”

news.title: SC grants relief to Ramco, Prism Cement, others in tax dispute with Maharashtra government
news.para: It said that the requirement of submitting these forms would apply prospectively after May 11, 2002, the date when amendments were made to the Central Sales Act, 1956.

news.title: Finnish paint maker Tikkurila and PPG complete Russia exit
news.para: "Tikkurila Oyj completed its exit from Russia at the end of January," PPG's senior manager Andrew Wood said in an emailed statement to Reuters, declining to share any details about the transaction.

news.title: Odisha High Court blocks attempt to weaken OAOM act
news.para: Officials noted that misconceptions about the OAOM Act's retrospective effect have led to inconsistent interpretation by registration officers across the state.

news.title: Protean eGov Technologies leases 68,021 sq ft office space in Mumbai
news.para: Colliers India, a real estate services firm, helped transacted the deal. The company's design services team will also design the project.

news.title: West Bengal forms panel to check building complaints outside Kolkata civic body
news.para: The committee will also look into minor deviations from the sanctioned plan or execution of any minor work in contravention of any sanctioned plan under the provisions of the West Bengal Municipal (Building) Rules, 2007.

news.title: Hubballi Dharwad civic body to pioneer Karnataka's first 3D GIS survey
news.para: Hubballi-Dharwad Municipal Corporation (HDMC) is set to become the state's pioneer in conducting a comprehensive 3D GIS survey, with plans to begin in the first week of March.

news.title: Nagpur civic body yet to recover Rs 224 crore in property tax dues
news.para: The NMC has intensified its recovery drive by issuing warrants and attaching properties to meet its target. But, a significant amount remains unpaid.

news.title: Kerala government likely to approve Thiruvananthapuram metro rail project soon
news.para: Once the chief minister approves the alignment, it will be tabled for cabinet approval, which is expected by the end of this month.

news.title: Commission asks Jodhpur development body to refund excess amount of plot to consumer

news.title: SC stays HC's contempt order on South Mumbai flats' 'illegal' merger
news.para: Sukhshanti CHSL had complained to BMC that its members, Mahimtura and Gangji, owners of a flat on the ground floor, amalgamated an adjoining flat owned by a deceased member.

news.title: Bhubaneswar development body approved 2,858 building plans in eight years without authority: RTI reply
news.para: According to regulations, the authority for plan approvals was transferred to the Bhubaneswar Municipal Corporation (BMC) in 2015 within the civic body's jurisdiction, yet BDA persisted in issuing approvals, violating established protocols.

news.title: Almost all of 200-acre Silicon Valley allotted to IT firms: West Bengal CM
news.para: "We initially thought of setting up Silicon Valley on 100 acres. We revised the size and made provisions for 200 acres. Almost the entire land has been allocated to companies," Banerjee said after the Budget was tabled.

news.title: Demand for mixed-use developments rises in Pune
news.para: Mixed-use projects incorporate multiple functionalities, such as residential housing, retail hubs and recreational facilities, into one community.

news.title: Developer, RWAs served notice for flouting building code in Gurugram
news.para: The notice, issued under Section 10(2) of the Haryana Development and Regulations of Urban Areas Act, 1975, highlights violations of approved building plans and warns of legal action if corrective measures are not taken immediately.
